# Documentation Guidelines

## When to Fetch Documentation

### Next.js & Web Development Documentation

Fetch Next.js and web development documentation when:

1. **Next.js Specific Features**:
   - App Router patterns and conventions
   - Server Components vs Client Components
   - Middleware configuration
   - API routes and server actions
   - Build optimization and deployment

2. **Web Development Patterns**:
   - Responsive design techniques
   - Performance optimization for web
   - SEO best practices
   - Accessibility (a11y) guidelines
   - Browser compatibility issues

3. **Advanced Web Topics**:
   - Progressive Web App (PWA) features
   - Web APIs and browser capabilities
   - Security best practices
   - Caching strategies
   - Internationalization (i18n)

### When NOT to Fetch Documentation

- General React patterns (use standard React docs)
- TypeScript questions (use TypeScript docs)
- CSS/styling questions (use Tailwind docs)
- Authentication patterns (use Clerk docs)
- Backend questions (use Convex docs)

## Documentation Sources

- **Next.js**: Official Next.js documentation and examples
- **React**: React documentation for general React patterns
- **TypeScript**: TypeScript handbook for type-related questions
- **Tailwind CSS**: Tailwind documentation for styling
- **Web Standards**: MDN Web Docs for web APIs and standards

## Best Practices

- Always check official documentation first
- Look for recent updates and breaking changes
- Verify compatibility with current versions
- Cross-reference multiple sources when needed
- Focus on official sources over community tutorials